cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use J-ART, please cite this archived release."
title: "J-ART: A Japanese Adversarial Red-Team Framework for Application-Layer LLM Security and Cost-Efficiency"
abstract: >-
  J-ART is an open, reproducible harness that evaluates the application-structure
  layer of LLM deployments (model x system-prompt strength x guardrail x
  retrieval) rather than bare models, using Japanese-specific obfuscation
  transforms, MITRE ATLAS-grounded attacks with harmless proxy markers, a
  five-way guardrail comparison, Wilson confidence intervals, and a
  cost-efficiency metric.
type: software
